Package: tweetWrangleR
Title: Wrangle Tweets Collected from Streaming API
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Sefa", "Ozalp", email = "ozalpas@cardiff.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package wrangles tweets collected from Twitter's streaming API. 
    Twitter data in .jsonl files is parsed and flattened into a 2D tibble.
    The package is constantly under development and suggestions, pull/feature requests are encouraged. 
    Features that will be added to the package in the future are:
        * Clean tweet text
        * Derive topic models
        * Prepare RT data for social network analysis
        * Calculate RT counts
        * Calculate RT lags
        * Derive user gender based on names
        * Calculate sentiment scores
        * Text classification using externally built classifiers.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.4)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
